" role="group" aria-label="Basic example"> <a role="button" class="btn btn-light w-100" href="https://btemplates.com/2016/blogger-template-its-a-girl/demo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Demo</a> <a role="button" class="btn btn-light w-100" href="https://btemplates.com/2016/blogger-template-its-a-girl/">Download</a></div></div></div></div><div class="container mb-3 mb-sm-4"><nav aria-label="Page navigation example"><ul class="pagination justify-content-center"><li class="page-item disabled"> <a href="https://btemplates.com/" class="page-link"> Newer templates </a></li><li class="page-item disabled"> <a class="page-link" href="#">Page 1 of 184</a></li><li class="page-item"> <a href="https://btemplates.com/page/2/" class="page-link"> Older templates </a></li></ul></nav></div><div id="home-faq"><div class="container-fluid" id="what-is-blogger"><div class="container"><h2>What is Blogger and why should you use it?</h2><p><dfn>Blogger</dfn> is a publishing platform that allows you to create a blog under the subdomain <code>blogspot.com</code> or your own domain. It was created in 1999 by Pyra Lab and acquired by
 Google in 2003.</p><p>Some of the advantages of using Blogger are:</p><ul><li>Free service with almost 100% uptime.</li><li>It uses Google's infrastructure. Very fast page loading.</li><li><a href="https://btemplates.com/blogger-templates/ads-ready/">Adsense
 already</a> integrated into the platform.</li><li>No limits on disk space, bandwidth, number of visits per month, published posts and up to 100
 blogs per account.</li></ul></div></div><div class="container-fluid" id="blogger-templates-def"><div class="container"><h2>What is a Blogger template?</h2><p>A <dfn>Blogger template</dfn> is a design in <abbr title="Extensible Markup Language">XML</abbr> format consisting of <abbr title="Cascading Style Sheets">CSS</abbr>, <abbr
 title="Extensible Markup Language">XML</abbr> and Javascript code that can be
 used to create a blog, website or application using the <a href="https://blogger.com/">Blogger.com</a> platform.</p></div></div><div class="container-fluid" id="free-templates"><div class="container"><h2>Are all Blogger templates free?</h2><p>All templates on BTemplates are free to download. But keep in mind that they are under a specific
 use license, e.g.: <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.en.html">GPL</a>, Creative Commons, etc.</p><p>You can find the license in the XML code, in the readme file and/or on the documentation page.</p></div></div><div class="container-fluid" id="blogger-templates-features"><div class="container"><h2>How do I choose a template for Blogger?</h2><p>Every blog has different needs, but there are common features to consider when determining which template is best for you.</p><ul><li><h3><a href="https://btemplates.com/blogger-templates/responsive/">Responsive design</a></h3><p>Responsive design allows you to provide a consistent experience across desktop and mobile
 devices and
 to reach a wider audience.</p></li><li><h3><a href="https://btemplates.com/tag/simple/">Fast loading</a></h3><p>A design that loads quickly provides a better experience, resulting in fewer
 readers leaving your site early and better search engine rankings.</p></li><li><h3><a href="https://btemplates.com/blogger-templates/seo-friendly/">SEO friendly</a></h3><p>A template with well-constructed titles, fast loading, well-organized code, etc. can help
 you
 greatly in the task of optimizing your site for search engines.</p></li><li><h3>Well designed gadgets</h3><p>If the template's gadgets are well integrated into the design you will be able to take better
 advantage
 of Blogger as a platform and provide a better service to your readers.</p></li><li><h3>Support provided</h3><p>If the template's author offers support or installation (usually available in the
 non-free version), it can save you hours of work and a lot of headaches.</p></li></div></div><div class="container-fluid" id="customize-blogger-templates"><div class="container"><h2>How do I customize a Blogger theme?</h2><p>There are several ways to customize a Blogger theme, but the way you make changes varies from template
 to template. In general:</p><p>1. Read the information inside the documentation link carefully. This will tell you how the author
 prepared the template to be modified.</p><p>2. Try the template designer in Blogger. Most modern templates support color and font changes at:</p><p><em>Blogger &rarr; Theme &rarr; Template Designer</em></p><p>3. Go to the Layout section and explore and change the settings of the main gadgets to your
 liking.</p><p><em>Blogger &rarr; Layout</em></p><p>4. For large or more advanced changes it is advisable to learn a little <a
 href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML">HTML</a> and <a
 href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</a>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="footer" class="container-fluid bg-dark text-white"><div class="container"><div class="row justify-content-center" id="footer-subscription"><div class="col-12 col-sm-10 col-md-8"><h5>Subscribe by email</h5><p>Receive the latest templates, news and discounts directly in your inbox.</p><form class="form-inline" id="footer-email"> <label class="sr-only" for="name">Name</label> <input type="text" class="form-control" id="name" value="No modify" required/> <label class="sr-only" for="email-subscriber">Email</label> <input type="text" class="form-control" id="email-subscriber" placeholder="Email"/> <button type="submit" class="btn btn-success"> <span class="spinner-border spinner-border-sm d-none" role="status" aria-hidden="true"></span> <span class="sr-only">Loading...</span> <span class="subscribe-msg">Subscribe</span> </button><div class="invalid-feedback">Please enter a valid email address.</div></form><div class="modal" tabindex="-1" id="subscription-modal"><div class="modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered"><div class="modal-content"><div class="modal-header"><h5 class="modal-title">Subscription status</h5> <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"> <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span> </button></div><div  id="subscription-status" class="modal-body"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="row" id="extra"><div class="col-12"><ul class="nav justify-content-center"><li class="nav-item"> <a rel="nofollow" class="nav-link text-light" href="https://btemplates.com/terms-of-use-es/">Terms of use</a></li><li class="nav-item"> <a class="nav-link text-light" href="https://btemplates.com/privacy-policy/">Privacy policy</a></li></ul></div></div></div></div> <a href='javascript:void(0)' id='back-top' style='display: block;'> <svg class="icon icon-angle-up"><use xlink:href="https://btemplates.com/wp-content/themes/peualiztli/images/symbol-de